{"timestamp": "2026-07-18 18:03:31,982", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.execution", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_execution_result", "line": 199, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-07-18T18:03:31.982314\", \"task_id\": \"task2\", \"agent_id\": \"7\", \"objective\": \"Conduct technical interview\", \"result\": \"- **Interview Preparation:**\\n  - Review the job description to understand essential technical skills, tools, and domain knowledge required for the role.\\n  - Analyze the candidate's resume to identify their relevant technical experience, projects, specific technologies used, and areas for deeper inquiry.\\n  - Develop a structured set of technical questions tailored to the job requirements and the candidate's background, covering core technical skills, problem-solving, and system design (if applicable).\\n  - Prepare specific coding challenges, architecture discussions, or theoretical questions based on the role's needs.\\n  - Define clear evaluation criteria or a rubric for assessing technical responses to ensure objectivity.\\n  - Set up the necessary interview environment, including any online coding platforms, whiteboard tools, or screen-sharing capabilities.\\n\\n- **Candidate Introduction and Setting Expectations:**\\n  - Greet the candidate and introduce yourself and your role.\\n  - Briefly exp...\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"duration_seconds\": 0.0}"}
